    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ENGINE COOLING SYSTEM - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl1200303">
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcproc id="hl1200304" svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
            <title>EFFECTS OF COOLING SYSTEM NEGLECT</title>
            <para>Neglect of cooling system maintenance causes gradual damage, so the effects are often overlooked until
                major repairs are necessary. Many problems are caused by overheating, but overcooling is troublesome and
                more difficult to diagnose.
            </para>
            <para>OVERHEATING can cause the following problems:</para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Burned valves.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Poor lubrication and increased engine wear.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Sticking valves and lifters.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Hot spots in the engine.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <para>OVERCOOLING can cause the following:</para>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Excessive fuel consumption.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Sludge formation in the crankcase.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Corrosive acid formation in the crankcase.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <para>To maintain proper operation of the cooling system, install the correct replacement parts for service
                or repair. DO NOT use radiator cores, tanks or hoses other than those recommended.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Check the coolant level daily. The sight glass marks the low coolant level. Correct as
                        necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
